            "id": "4409749",
            "title": "HP plans to acquire Humane, but not its AI pin: report",
            "description": "<html><body><p>HP Inc. (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HPQ\" title=\"HP Inc.\">HPQ</a></span>) plans to acquire the Silicon Valley startup Humane, but the deal does not include its wearable artificial intelligence-powered clip on computer, known as the Ai Pin, according to Bloomberg.</p> <p>HP is acquiring Humane's software platform and intellectual<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> property for $116M, according to the </span><a class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-02-18/hp-116-million-deal-for-humane-includes-ip-but-no-ai-pin-device\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"report\">report</a><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">. HP also plans to retain most of its employees. However, Humane's </span><a class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4109376-humane-explore-sale-after-rocky-launch-of-ai-wearable-device-bloomberg\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Ai pin business\">Ai pin business</a><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> is coming to an end. The Humane team is expected to form a new division at HP with the goal of implementing AI tech in HP's products.</span></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The Ai pin was released in November 2023. The device, meant to be worn on clothing, could be tapped to talk to a virtual assistant and beam text and images on a user's palm through a laser projection system. However, the wearable computer, which cost $699 and a $24 per month subscription, racked up numerous bad reviews and was poorly received.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">However, the technology behind the pin was considered ahead of its time, and could be implemented into other products, which is what HP reportedly plans to do.</p> </body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/987512596/image_987512596.jpg",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4409749-hp-plans-to-acquire-humane-but-not-its-ai-pin-report",
            "pub_date": "2025-02-19 01:14:57",
